# OT Sentinel — Known DNP3 Outstations CDB List
# =============================================
# Format: DATA_LINK_ADDRESS:Description
#
# Used by rule 200012 (OT-SENTINEL-DNP-001) to detect unsolicited responses
# from rogue/unknown outstation devices.
#
# The data link address is the DNP3 layer-2 address identifying each device.
#
# Deployment: Copy to /var/ossec/etc/lists/ and add to ossec.conf:
#   <list>etc/lists/known_dnp3_outstations</list>
#
# Tuning:
# - Populate with all legitimate outstation addresses from your asset inventory
# - Empty list = all unsolicited responses will alert (discovery mode)

